Pirate (South America)
The Pirates of the South American coastline are raiders, traders, and
survivors who operate the sea lanes between the continent's many factions.
They are equal parts skilled sailor, fighter, and opportunist.

Pirates choose from Physical, Rogue, Pilot, and Weapons skill categories.
They are trained in seamanship, navigation, and personal combat. A Pirate
without a ship is still a very dangerous person on land.

Attribute requirements: PS 10, PP 10.
Starting equipment: Sailor's clothing, a cutlass or vibro-blade, one ranged
weapon, personal radio, rope, and a nautical chart of the local coastline.
